com.google.iot.cbor

Interface CborReader


  • public interface CborReader
    Interface for parsing CBOR data into CborObject instances.
    See Also:
    CborWriter, CborObject.createFromCborByteArray(byte[]), CborObject.createFromCborByteArray(byte[], int, int)

      • createFromByteArray

        static CborReader createFromByteArray(byte[] bytes,
                                      int offset,
                                      int objectCount)
        Creates a CborReader instance from a byte array with starting offset and a total object count. The resulting CborReader will be configured to emit objectCount data items. If the input data does not contain objectCount objects, a CborParseException will be thrown from readDataItem()}.
        Parameters:
        bytes - the byte array to parse
        offset - where in bytes to start parsing
        objectCount - the number of top-level data items that will be generated
        Returns:
        a new CborReader instance

      • hasRemainingDataItems

        boolean hasRemainingDataItems()
        Determines if there are additional data items to parse.
        Returns:
        true if there are additional data items which can be retrieved via readDataItem(), false otherwise.

      • readDataItem

        CborObject readDataItem()
                 throws CborParseException,
                        IOException
        Reads the next available data item as a CborObject. This method will block until an entire data item is read.
        Returns:
        the read data item
        Throws:
        CborParseException - if the data item was corrupted
        IOException - if there was a problem with the underlying input mechanism
        NoSuchElementException - if there are no more data items to be read

      • bytesParsed

        Gets the number of bytes that have been parsed by this instance.
        Returns:
        the number of parsed bytes
